#overview.container{ :style => 'display:none;' }
  .well
    %h2 Passmaster
    %h5 Enter your email address to access your accounts or to get started.
    = form_tag(users_path, :remote => true, :id => 'overview_form') do
      %p= email_field_tag(:email, '', :placeholder => 'Email Address', :class => 'input-xlarge', :id => 'overview_email', :required => true)
      %p= submit_tag('Access Accounts', :class => 'btn btn-primary', :id => 'overview_btn')

  .well
    %h5
      Passmaster is a simple tool for storing all of your account details securely in the cloud.
      With Passmaster, all of your sensitive account details are encrypted with a single master password
      making it easy to have strong, unique passwords for each site you visit. Passmaster is built with
      HTML5 and is designed to be always accessible both online and offline on desktop browsers and mobile
      devices. Check out the features below.

    #features
      .feature.pull-left
        .feature-inner
          %h5 Store Everything
          %p
            Passmaster is designed to store usernames and passwords for all the websites you use but can store
            other related information as well. There's room for account numbers, security questions, website
            URLs, or anything else you else you might need.
      .feature.pull-left
        .feature-inner
          %h5 Secure Password Generator
          %p
            Use the built-in generator to create cryptographically secure random passwords for all your accounts.
            If any one of your passwords is compromised you can easily generate a new one while the rest of your
            accounts remain safe. The length and character set is configurable to match each site's requirements.
      .feature.pull-left
        .feature-inner
          %h5 Host-Proof Encryption
          %p
            Your account details are for your eyes only so everything is encrypted on your computer or mobile
            device with your master password before being saved to the cloud. Only you know the master
            password so no one, not even the server admins, can determine anything about your account details.
      .feature.pull-left
        .feature-inner
          %h5 Offline Access
          %p
            Passmaster uses HTML5 application caching and local storage to make your account details accessible
            even while you are offline. Every time you use Passmaster it automatically syncs your data so it is
            available whenever you need it.
      .feature.pull-left
        .feature-inner
          %h5 Automatic Backups
          %p
            Enable automatic backups to receive an email with your encrypted account details each time you make a change.
            This is a great way to ensure you always have a backup of your data and you can always use one of the backups
            if you need recover something in the future. You can also download a backup file to your computer at any time
            from the Backup menu once logged in.
      .feature.pull-left
        .feature-inner
          %h5 Multi-factor Authentication
          %p
            Increase the security of your account by enabling multi-factor authentication with Google Authenticator.
            Each new device used to access your accounts will require a random key generated by the Google Authenticator
            app on your mobile phone.
      .feature.pull-left
        .feature-inner
          %h5 Open and Portable
          %p
            Passmaster isn't going anywhere but in the event of an extended outage you will always be able to access your
            accounts details. Each Passmaster backup contains everything you need to view all of your accounts.
            Just open the included HTML file and use it to decrypt your backup. The source code of the included account
            viewer contains all of the javascript required to decrypt your data and is well commented, so check it out
            if you're curious about what's going on under the hood.
      .feature.pull-left
        .feature-inner
          %h5 Works Everywhere
          %p
            Passmaster works on any modern browser that supports HTML5 on all operating systems. There are also mobile apps
            available for Android in the
            %a{ :target => 'blank', :href => 'https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=io.passmaster.Passmaster' } Play Store
            and iOS in the
            %a{ :target => 'blank', :href => 'https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/passmaster/id615271561?mt=8' } App Store
            so you will always have access to your accounts.
    .clearfix
